    <PrimAttribute name="doNotFIlterCombos" id="d0285344-4761-4a9e-a9ba-a66b94b892d6">
        <embedded/>
        <type name="Boolean"/>
        <access>readonly</access>
        <text>Filtering is on for all CMUI_ComboBox and CMUI_FieldComboBoxControl, filter can be turned off individually if necessary OR all can have filtering turned off using this system configurable option.

The filter is achieved by setting the 'itemLevel' for the non matching items to 2. This basically removes them from the combo list, but they are still in the collection on the combo box, so all items can be reshown by setting itemLevel to 1.

</text>
    </PrimAttribute>
